name: CryptoMushrooms #006 - Marasmius Hudsonii
description:
This beautiful, delicate and tiny mushroom also know as “Holly Parachute” is a rare find. As the name suggests, is shaped like a parachute and it grows in the moist of dead holly leaves. Its cap size is usually no more than 6mm in diameter and often less than a half that size. The interesting and exotic feature that makes it special is that it’s cap and the stem is covered in microscopic erect bristle-like red-brown hairs (setae). You can find these distinctive little mushrooms in woodlands and hedgerows. It’s widespread throughout Britain and Ireland and in many parts of mainland Europe, but not recorded very occasionally. Is also found in some parts of North America.
